title: For Sale/Trade:  AK-47 Receiver for (Romainian), Polish, Bulgarian, w/standard stock Trunnion
location: NW Oklahoma City, Oklahoma, Oklahoma City, Oklahoma City, Oklahoma
postcontent:
I got these to do a couple builds but decided not to get the ak kits.
These are the highest quality receivers for your ak build anywhere all USA.
I HAVE TWO. 80.00 Each

The front and rear trunnion holes on these flats are pre-punched to help with the installation of the trunnions.
**Receiver flat thickness= 1mm (.040")
**Material 4130 Annealed 
**Comes with bolt guide rails 
**Rails and flat need to be heat treated. Then Welded to Receiver.
To use these flats you will need to have a 5mm and 7mm reamer.  The physics of bending sheet metal make it next to impossible to have a bend close to a hole without distorting slightly.  To solve this the holes on the flat are undersized and need to be reamed to size. 
The rails that come with the flats are pictured below. They have mag stabilizers on both rails to keep the mag from tilting and causing feed problems.  Before installing the rails you will need to trim the mag stabilizers to match the thickness of the Mag you are using. (7.62 or 5.56)

title: For Sale:  Romanian FPK/PSL-54C **Sold-Pending Payment**
postcontent:
I'm leaving this listed locally for now, but this PSL has tentatively been sold on GunBroker, pending receipt of funds and the correct FFL transfer paperwork. In the event that deal falls through, I will still take interested party emails / questions, and might consider trades too, but we'll see how it goes on GunBroker.
*****************************************************
Romanian PSL-54C / FPK Dragunov - TG Knox receiver 'Made In Romania'. The scope and all accessories are included with this set: Complete bayonet / scabbard / frog, leather sling, complete cleaning kit w/3-piece cleaning rod, a 4 mag capacity field pouch, three 10 round capacity magazines (1 is unnumbered - 2 non-matching), a Romanian TIP2 6x24 (dated 1975) side rail mounted scope, canvas scope cover, scope cleaning cloth and a yellow scope lens filter. The tritium illumination on the scope has expired. Also includes a new adjustable bipod (8-12"), a TGI FPK / Dragunov manual and a manual for zeroing the Russian SVD style reticle scope. The cleaning kit has: 7.62x54R broken cartridge extractor, gas port reamer, cleaning jag, brush, pin tool, grease bottle, tube / cap and a black pouch to keep all of it in, PLUS a spare sight post, bolt extractor retaining pin, bolt extractor spring and a firing pin retainer. Everything is either new, unissued or unused and will be shipped in a hard case (Plano plastic/foam lined).

All serial numbered components on the rifle match, with the exception of the bolt itself, and the 'Made in Romania' TG Knox receiver serial number. Original Romanian hammer forged chrome lined barrel with sharp rifling and it's mirror bright. It has a matching numbered threaded muzzle brake (14x1mm LH thread with a spring pin lock) and an INTACT bayonet lug. The receiver has the original bolt hold open center support piece, but does NOT include the little parts (spring, pin and lifter foot). The Romanian parkerized finish was also completely blued over externally. The outside of the barrel where it was originally pressed into the front trunnion exhibits a minimal gall, but it does not affect fit, finish or function. The barrel trunnion is attached with grade 8 screws. All other receiver attachments are riveted. There are a few very minor small dents in the wood handguards (~ 1/8" long). The stock furniture is in exceptional condition otherwise, with no cracks or repairs and matches relatively well, with the butt stock about a slight shade darker. I fired 10 rounds to check fit and function, as this rifle was completely new and unfired. I will include the cartridges for inspection, so the ejection can be 'fine tuned' to adjust the direction and distance of the ejected cartridges. All in all, a very NICE PSL / FPK in outstanding condition that shoots / runs perfectly. It has been listed as used, since it was test fired to ensure safe operation, but it is essentially new. Buy it and break it in! PSL's are like AK's. It takes at least a couple hundred rounds to get it loosened up and running free, then you just never worry about it again, since it's a Kalashnikov action built on the same receivers as the Romanian RPK.

Payment to be Cash / USPS Money Order / Cashier's Check, or I can accept credit cards or bank transfer cash through PayPal (Invoiced with DISCREET payment only, with NO mention of GB, firearms or anything else related, since I need my PayPal account for FeeBay and don't want it locked down or closed). For any type of PayPal transaction, the buyer will have to add an additional 4% to cover their transaction 'fee'. I will invoice the buyer directly, which will include all required fees. All applicable firearms FFL transfer and shipping regulations apply, and the buyer is responsible for determining if the firearm is legal to own in their area, plus complying with whatever your various local regulations are. No sales to California residents or any other place where semi-auto rifles are prohibited or magazine restrictions say you can't exercise your 2nd Amendment rights. The entire package will be shipped for free, but note the requirement below for an additional FFL transfer fee on my end if required, which will be extra.

For all of you new gun owners, virgin bidders and out of state interested parties, I am an individual seller, so check with your receiving FFL to see if they'll accept the rifle shipment FROM an individual. BATF regulations allow shipments from any individual to any FFL, but some FFL licensees just won't do it. If yours won't, an additional $25 fee WILL be added for having to transport to and ship through an FFL on my end. After the purchase, you will have to inform me of how it has to be shipped, then have your FFL send me (or the FLL on my end) their signed license form and address information (hardcopy or email). I will invoice you for the total amount due AFTER you get the FFL / shipping figured out, so if you're serious, check with your FFL PRIOR TO BIDDING! I'm shipping it for free in a hard case already, so don't push it and don't drag it out. I'll give the winning bidder THREE DAYS to confirm the shipping method and payment form. That part can usually be handled with a quick phone call to verify if your FFL will or won't receive shipment. For you guys who have an FFL (not just a C&R), you know the drill, and thanks for reading through my rant to the newbies. If you're in Missouri, we can do this face to face and not mess with the shipping restrictions. That would be nice... THANKS for looking!
